Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Conan Episode 821 "The \NHidden Secret of Dongaraji Temple"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.37,0:00:07.70,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Have you seen this man?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.76,0:00:11.36,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Four days ago, on Tuesday night...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.37,0:00:13.87,DCNote,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Beika Finance
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.68,0:00:18.25,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. On that night, he stole 30 \Nmillion yen from a bank in Beika.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.47,0:00:23.08,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you know already, but \Ntwo hours after the robbery,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.55,0:00:27.31,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,the culprit Shishido Takashi \Ndied in an accident,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.31,0:00:29.81,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,but the 30 million yen he \Nstole is still missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.50,0:00:34.51,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.99,0:00:36.85,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,We may not recover the money today, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.85,0:00:39.37,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Let's check by the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.37,0:00:40.31,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.49,0:00:43.40,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.40,0:00:44.81,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.39,0:00:49.69,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing, mister?\NDid a new pachinko parlor open?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.07,0:00:53.32,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot! I've been summoned \Nto Dongaraji Temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.66,0:00:56.23,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They received a phone threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.06,0:01:00.53,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Someone sent Dongaraji\NTemple a phone threat?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.51,0:01:04.43,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A canvas stained black with crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.43,0:01:06.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,With brilliant detective \Nskills, its color is changed!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.14,0:01:08.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Today's episode is set at Dongaraji Temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.92,0:01:10.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A dangerous secret hides inside the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.99,0:01:14.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth with the \Nbody of a child and the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.51,0:01:17.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.98,0:03:02.99,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(405,1)}The Hidden Secret of Dongaraji Temple
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.92,0:03:00.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Hidden Secret of Dongaraji Temple!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.49,0:03:06.74,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They demanded you stop remodeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.01,0:03:14.08,DCMain,RYOZEN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Yes. Construction started just yesterday, \Nbut late last night, we got a call.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.50,0:03:14.08,Ryozen,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Adachi Ryozen (60)\NDongaraji Temple\NHead Priest
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.85,0:03:16.10,DCItalic,RYOZEN,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.10,0:03:18.09,DCItalic,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Stop construction immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.27,0:03:20.35,DCItalic,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't, you'll be cursed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.52,0:03:24.84,DCMain,RYOZEN,0000,0000,0000,,I reported it to the police, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.14,0:03:29.62,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Just the threat of a curse isn't \Nenough to make the police act.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.06,0:03:32.10,DCMain,RYOZEN,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be too late if we wait \Nuntil something happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.47,0:03:34.43,DCMain,RYOZEN,0000,0000,0000,,so we've halted construction temporarily,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.43,0:03:39.36,DCMain,RYOZEN,0000,0000,0000,,and were hoping you could \Nfind whoever made the threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.12,0:03:44.28,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I understand. Leave it to me, Mori Kogoro.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.49,0:03:48.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm kind of curious. I wonder what \Nkind of threat the temple got.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.90,0:03:51.16,DCMain,WOMAN A,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.54,0:03:54.99,DCMain,WOMAN A,0000,0000,0000,,Mother, are you accusing me of lying?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.99,0:04:00.05,DCMain,WOMAN B,0000,0000,0000,,How could a single person \Nappear in two places at once?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.29,0:04:02.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds like an interesting conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.97,0:04:06.37,DCMain,WOMAN B,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing interesting about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.62,0:04:09.18,DCMain,WOMAN B,0000,0000,0000,,Yesterday afternoon,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.45,0:04:14.19,DCMain,WOMAN B,0000,0000,0000,,Toratani-san who lives down the street, \Nwas lying in the sun at Chuo Park.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.50,0:04:17.61,DCMain,WOMAN A,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, you mistook someone else for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.61,0:04:21.53,DCMain,WOMAN A,0000,0000,0000,,Toratani Eisaku-san was at \NNishiguchi Park at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.53,0:04:23.51,DCMain,WOMAN A,0000,0000,0000,,I saw it with my own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.51,0:04:29.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Which means one of you mistook \Nsomeone else for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.28,0:04:31.54,DCMain,WOMAN B,0000,0000,0000,,But I didn't just see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.70,0:04:35.54,DCMain,WOMAN B,0000,0000,0000,,It was from far away,\Nbut we greeted each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.91,0:04:37.29,DCMain,WOMAN A,0000,0000,0000,,So did I!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.02,0:04:42.80,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,One person in two places at once?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.50,0:04:47.67,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.67,0:04:52.35,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So two men suddenly became flustered \Nwhen they saw construction had begun?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.35,0:04:53.06,DCMain,WOMAN C,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.39,0:04:59.78,DCMain,WOMAN C,0000,0000,0000,,Yesterday evening, I saw two men when I \Npassed by the gate of Dongaraji Temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.70,0:05:02.82,DCItalic,KINTA,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.11,0:05:05.07,DCItalic,GINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad, Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.35,0:05:09.07,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So they made a phone threat to \Nmake them stop construction.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.33,0:05:13.95,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It could have been them. \NDo you know who they were?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.26,0:05:16.53,DCMain,WOMAN C,0000,0000,0000,,They're brothers called Kinta and Ginsuke.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.53,0:05:17.27,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.27,0:05:19.95,DCMain,WOMAN C,0000,0000,0000,,They're Toratani-san's \Nsons, from second street.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.46,0:05:22.71,DCNote,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Toratani Eisaku
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.15,0:05:22.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.91,0:05:26.77,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.77,0:05:27.22,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.78,0:05:29.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mister, what are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.39,0:05:35.73,Ginsuke,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(273,1)}Toratani Ginsuke (31)\NToratani Family Second Son
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.39,0:05:35.73,Ginsuke - Copy,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(273,1)}Toratani Kinta (33)\NToratani Family Eldest Son
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.46,0:05:33.28,DCMain,KINTA,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}What does a detective want with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.28,0:05:36.36,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}There seems to be some reason the \Nconstruction at Dongaraji Temple
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.74,0:05:38.73,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}wouldn't be good for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.92,0:05:39.73,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.16,0:05:43.65,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Did you make a threatening phone call?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.39,0:05:50.57,DCMain,KINTA,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't me. That's that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.61,0:05:53.04,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not finished here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.29,0:05:54.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is Eisaku-san home?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.83,0:05:58.46,DCMain,KINTA,0000,0000,0000,,What? Why are you asking about our dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.46,0:06:00.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I heard a strange story.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.98,0:06:05.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There are two people who claim \Nto have seen him at the same time
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.74,0:06:08.09,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,at Chuo Park and Nishiguchi Park.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.34,0:06:11.17,DCMain,KINTA,0000,0000,0000,,Ginsuke, did you...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.17,0:06:13.51,DCMain,GINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,You, too, Brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.74,0:06:18.19,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure what's going on, \Nbut we'll know once we meet him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.78,0:06:20.78,DCMain,GINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,He's out right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.78,0:06:24.64,DCMain,KINTA,0000,0000,0000,,Our dad is full of energy, \Nso he's always going out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.64,0:06:26.71,DCMain,GINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,He's always going out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.71,0:06:28.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.75,0:06:31.55,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm more interested in \Nyou two than your dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.55,0:06:33.70,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Threatening someone is a crime, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.09,0:06:37.25,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.59,0:06:42.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You get a bunch of newspapers delivered.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.35,0:06:46.89,DCMain,GINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,We don't get papers delivered. \NThat was a special day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.89,0:06:47.77,DCMain,KINITA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.37,0:06:52.11,DCMain,KINTA,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, we've got nothing \Nto do with Dongaraji Temple!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.16,0:06:56.34,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They seem totally guilty to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.34,0:06:59.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They're definitely hiding something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.86,0:07:07.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,According to the neighbors,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.30,0:07:11.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,the Toratani family and Dongaraji Temple \Nhave nothing to do with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.65,0:07:13.53,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Aside from being near each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.81,0:07:16.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But that family is a little strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.98,0:07:21.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's three of them living \Nthere, but nobody works.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.44,0:07:24.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Eisaku-san is old, so I understand him,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.77,0:07:32.41,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,but the brothers Kinta and Ginsuke have no \Nmotivation and never keep a job for long.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.70,0:07:35.93,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,How are they paying for food?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.31,0:07:39.35,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,With Eisaku's pension.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.56,0:07:42.41,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The brothers are living off his pension?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.41,0:07:45.11,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What a pathetic couple of brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.11,0:07:47.95,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What are they going to do when their dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.45,0:07:49.36,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.62,0:07:52.53,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Eisaku isn't alive anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.02,0:07:54.05,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.65,0:07:56.92,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He probably died from some sudden illness,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.92,0:07:59.49,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but the brothers didn't report \Nit to the public office.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.49,0:08:01.66,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They'd lose his pension if they did.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.34,0:08:06.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,And they hid the body somewhere \Nin Dongaraji Temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.32,0:08:13.84,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But since construction started, \Nthe body might be unearthed,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.10,0:08:16.10,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,so they halted construction.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.10,0:08:18.59,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's insane. You don't \Nhave a shred of evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.59,0:08:23.22,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Wait. If he suddenly fell ill, \Nthey would've called an ambulance
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.22,0:08:25.80,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,instead of worrying about his pension...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.48,0:08:29.62,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The two of them killed \Nhim with their own hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.62,0:08:30.06,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.06,0:08:32.40,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He probably nagged them for not working!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.79,0:08:36.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you layering delusions \Non top of delusions?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.49,0:08:43.93,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But if you assume they're hiding\NEisaku-san's death, it does explain that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.93,0:08:46.42,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Explain what?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.72,0:08:51.82,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently Eisaku-san would \Nalways go sit in the sun
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.82,0:08:54.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,at Chuo Park and Nishiguchi \NPark on sunny days.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.74,0:08:57.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It would be suspicious if \Nhe didn't keep up the habit,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.60,0:08:59.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,so they pretended to be their father.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.11,0:09:06.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,One of the brothers appeared here, \Nwhile the other went to Nishiguchi Park.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.32,0:09:10.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But because the brothers hadn't \Ndiscussed it beforehand,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.21,0:09:13.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,they ended up appearing in two \Ndifferent places at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.75,0:09:16.58,DCItalic,KINTA,0000,0000,0000,,Ginsuke, did you...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.58,0:09:19.03,DCItalic,GINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,You, too, Brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.72,0:09:22.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,When you look at it that way, \Nit does explain their actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.61,0:09:29.23,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If you wanted to see Eisaku \Nand he's not around anymore,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.23,0:09:31.63,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,they had to trick you \Ninto thinking he was out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.91,0:09:35.80,DCItalic,KINTA,0000,0000,0000,,Our dad is full of energy, \Nso he's always going out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.80,0:09:37.38,DCItalic,GINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,He's always going out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.89,0:09:42.39,DCNote,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Toratani Eisaku
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.40,0:09:42.39,DCMain,KINTA,0000,0000,0000,,What now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.05,0:09:46.18,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You killed your own father, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.41,0:09:47.48,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.69,0:09:50.98,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,And you buried the body at Dongaraji Temple
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.37,0:09:54.23,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,so you could continue to \Nillegally live off his pension!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.13,0:09:57.81,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like we're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.30,0:10:01.51,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I feel sorry for the late Eisaku.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.06,0:10:04.76,DCMain,EISAKU,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, is breakfast ready yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.76,0:10:05.25,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.25,0:10:06.95,DCMain,EISAKU,0000,0000,0000,,Is breakfast...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.91,0:10:13.21,Eisaku,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(280,265)}Toratani Eisaku (70)\NKinta and Ginsuke's Father
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.07,0:10:10.12,DCMain,EISAKU,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Oh, we have guests.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.46,0:10:13.42,DCMain,EISAKU,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}I hope my sons aren't bothering you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.42,0:10:14.52,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.93,0:10:17.11,DCMain,GINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,That's our dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.11,0:10:18.06,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.42,0:10:20.84,DCMain,KINTA,0000,0000,0000,,He's not a ghost. He's got feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.78,0:10:22.99,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.54,0:10:29.05,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm always telling him not to irresponsibly \Nsuspect people, but you know how kids are.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.17,0:10:35.28,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You saw him?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.54,0:10:38.39,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Four days ago on Tuesday night?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.39,0:10:41.20,DCMain,MAN A,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it was near Dongaraji Temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.39,0:10:41.20,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Dongaraji Temple
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.60,0:10:45.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad Eisaku-san is all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.95,0:10:49.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Although he was asking about breakfast \Nwhen it's already afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.79,0:10:53.71,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Those brothers must be the \Nones who stopped construction.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.00,0:10:56.71,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But if they didn't bury a body, then why?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.33,0:10:58.97,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If we can't figure that out...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.05,0:11:02.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Detectives Takagi and Chiba.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.24,0:11:06.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They're looking for the 30 million \Nyen that vanished, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.39,0:11:11.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did they get a tip that \Nsomeone saw the culprit here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.37,0:11:14.99,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I got it! They hid the money!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.99,0:11:15.86,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.91,0:11:20.29,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The brothers were working with the robber.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.29,0:11:26.53,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,After the robbery, they took the 30 million \Nand hid it somewhere in Dongaraji Temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.14,0:11:30.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's not impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.02,0:11:35.42,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You get a bunch of newspapers delivered.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.73,0:11:40.09,DCItalic,GINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,We don't get papers delivered. \NThat was a special day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.35,0:11:43.59,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Those papers were from the \Nday after the robbery.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.20,0:11:47.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They were probably curious about \Nhow the investigation was going.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.57,0:11:49.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They tried to hide that, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.54,0:11:53.59,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That must be it, then! I'd \Nbetter tell Takagi and Chiba.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.59,0:11:55.02,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.55,0:12:08.19,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, the culprit Shishido \Nfled this way after the robbery.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.19,0:12:11.41,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then he handed the money to his accomplices
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.62,0:12:14.02,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,so he wouldn't get caught \Nby the security checkpoints.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.02,0:12:16.19,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,That's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.56,0:12:17.38,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.38,0:12:21.57,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Shishido didn't trust others, so \Nit's unlikely he had accomplices.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.57,0:12:22.30,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.62,0:12:24.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.01,0:12:26.59,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So he couldn't have been working with anyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.82,0:12:30.75,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It certainly would be great if we \Ncould tie the phone threat case
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.75,0:12:34.63,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,you're working on to the 30 million, \Nbut you don't always get what you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.04,0:12:36.60,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Let's check out the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.03,0:12:37.93,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.01,0:12:42.61,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I think about it, it is weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.61,0:12:44.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Even if they hid it here somewhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.66,0:12:47.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,instead of going through the trouble \Nof stopping the construction,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.68,0:12:50.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,they should just go get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.12,0:12:52.48,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If they weren't working with him, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.53,0:12:55.32,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They must've stolen it from him!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.32,0:12:56.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.54,0:12:59.54,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Their dad's pension wasn't \Nenough for them to have fun,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.82,0:13:05.66,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,so they stole the money from him \Nand hid it at the nearby temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.70,0:13:08.55,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He's out of control.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.55,0:13:13.56,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They've got guts to steal from \Na robber, but I'll catch them!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.05,0:13:17.69,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But those brothers didn't seem \Nbold enough to commit a robbery.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.91,0:13:20.11,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,People can do anything if they have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.90,0:13:21.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mister?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.81,0:13:25.45,DCMain,WOMAN B,0000,0000,0000,,Four days ago on Tuesday night?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.69,0:13:27.48,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't see them?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.73,0:13:31.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The brothers should've been wandering \Naround here looking for their prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.68,0:13:34.37,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He's setting them up to be evil brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.63,0:13:38.25,DCMain,WOMAN A,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that the day Eisaku-san \Ndisappeared again?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.25,0:13:39.25,DCMain,WOMAN B,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.51,0:13:41.01,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Disappeared?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.01,0:13:43.21,DCMain,WOMAN A,0000,0000,0000,,Toratani-san has dementia.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.21,0:13:46.22,DCMain,WOMAN A,0000,0000,0000,,At night he sometimes \Nwanders around the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.22,0:13:50.96,DCMain,WOMAN B,0000,0000,0000,,His sons went looking \Nfor him that night, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.50,0:13:57.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So they did it while they were looking for \Ntheir father and hid it at Dongaraji Temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.84,0:13:58.84,DCMain,WOMAN B,0000,0000,0000,,They didn't hide him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.84,0:14:00.79,DCMain,WOMAN B,0000,0000,0000,,They found him at Dongaraji Temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.79,0:14:01.65,DCMain,WOMAN A,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.24,0:14:03.61,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Found him?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.24,0:14:06.40,DCMain,WOMAN B,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Eisaku-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.77,0:14:08.86,DCItalic,GINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for all the trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.08,0:14:12.41,DCItalic,WOMAN B,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine. I'm glad you \Nwere able to find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.81,0:14:15.10,DCItalic,KINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,He was at Dongaraji Temple today.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.10,0:14:16.12,DCItalic,WOMAN B,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.35,0:14:20.35,DCItalic,EISAKU,0000,0000,0000,,He was burying a backpack.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.76,0:14:23.09,DCItalic,GINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,We have no idea what he's talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.09,0:14:27.51,DCItalic,KINTA,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have a backpack to bury, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.62,0:14:34.26,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Eisaku buried a backpack at Dongaraji Temple?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.91,0:14:39.10,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So those brothers had nothing \Nto do with it from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.10,0:14:41.27,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, could it be? Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.61,0:14:44.72,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The dad is behind everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.59,0:14:46.94,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.28,0:14:52.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Your reasoning doesn't make sense, mister!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.56,0:14:54.91,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So the old man fell victim to temptation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.32,0:14:58.66,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He robbed the robber!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.14,0:15:02.06,DCItalic,KINTA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Are you here, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.06,0:15:04.50,DCItalic,GINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,If you're here, answer us!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.05,0:15:09.76,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then he buried his treasure \Nsomewhere in Dongaraji Temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.05,0:15:12.48,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But then construction began.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.48,0:15:15.76,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He wanted to go get it, but \Nsomething was stopping him,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.10,0:15:19.52,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,so he made a phone threat \Nto stop construction.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.79,0:15:22.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If he buried and hid the treasure,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.40,0:15:26.44,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,he wouldn't be telling \Neveryone about the backpack.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.72,0:15:28.69,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.56,0:15:33.49,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,People start saying things they \Nshouldn't have as they get older.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.77,0:15:34.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.86,0:15:37.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm turning their father in to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.46,0:15:43.41,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Well, whatever...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.22,0:15:46.35,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No, I can't just let him go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.84,0:15:51.30,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Think. I probably already have \Nall the necessary pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.52,0:15:55.50,DCItalic,EISAKU,0000,0000,0000,,He was burying a backpack.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.82,0:15:57.76,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could that have been...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.16,0:16:00.31,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And the brothers realized that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.75,0:16:02.16,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then it all makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.39,0:16:06.67,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But why did they have to \Npretend to be their father?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.66,0:16:13.95,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,People start saying things they \Nshouldn't have as they get older.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.81,0:16:16.60,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They feared he would say something.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.62,0:16:20.83,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's starting to come together. \NAll that's left is...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.47,0:16:30.15,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I have business with your father!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.23,0:16:54.15,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This is probably where he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.29,0:16:55.86,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.12,0:17:03.37,DCMain,RYOZEN,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.64,0:17:08.29,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I, Mori Kogoro, shall identify the \Nculprit who left the phone threat
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.66,0:17:12.17,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and find the missing 30 million \Nyen in one fell swoop!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.08,0:17:20.13,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Both of these crimes were \Ncarried out by Toraâ€”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.98,0:17:26.18,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Tora... Tora... Tiger!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.38,0:17:29.52,DCMain,RYOZEN,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.99,0:17:32.53,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The incident occurred four nights ago
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.00,0:17:38.91,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,when Toratani Eisaku witnessed a \Ncertain sight while wandering around.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.51,0:17:43.91,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He saw a man burying a backpack \Nhere at Dongaraji Temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.27,0:17:47.26,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,A backpack? You mean Shishido?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.63,0:17:50.42,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,He hid the 30 million here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.68,0:17:54.92,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He told his sons and neighbors about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.16,0:17:58.84,DCItalic,EISAKU,0000,0000,0000,,He was burying a backpack.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.42,0:18:04.66,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,No one knew what he meant until the next day \Nwhen his sons realized what he was saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.35,0:18:09.85,DCNote,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,30 Million Yen Stolen\NCulprit Killed While Fleeing. \NWhere is the Missing Money...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.33,0:18:09.85,DCItalic,GINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,This robbery happened nearby, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.20,0:18:13.49,DCItalic,GINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I had 30 million yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.69,0:18:18.24,DCItalic,KINTA,0000,0000,0000,,The backpack the robber \Nstuffed the money in...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.69,0:18:23.74,DCItalic,KINTA,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, this guy was burying \Nthis last night, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.43,0:18:26.92,DCItalic,EISAKU,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I said.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.92,0:18:29.25,DCItalic,GINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,The police haven't found it yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.60,0:18:33.16,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, you thought to pocket the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.16,0:18:34.89,DCItalic,KINTA,0000,0000,0000,,Where did he bury it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.21,0:18:36.87,DCItalic,GINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Where at Dongaraji Temple?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.87,0:18:38.26,DCItalic,EISAKU,0000,0000,0000,,Where was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.24,0:18:42.28,DCItalic,KINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,We just have to wait for \Nhis memory to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.69,0:18:44.76,DCItalic,GINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,It comes and goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.16,0:18:47.39,DCItalic,KINTA,0000,0000,0000,,But if we leave him alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.64,0:18:49.77,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You became worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.26,0:18:54.74,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Eisaku might tell anyone that he \Nsaw the backpack being buried.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.23,0:18:57.78,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,And if he did, it might reach \Nthe ears of the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.30,0:19:03.78,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Fearing this, you kept him inside \Nso he wouldn't see anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.36,0:19:06.29,DCMain,RYOZEN,0000,0000,0000,,They imprisoned their own father?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.51,0:19:10.05,DCMain,GINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,W-We just didn't let him go outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.05,0:19:12.00,DCMain,KINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,W-We didn't tie him up or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.37,0:19:14.38,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So no one would find \Nout you imprisoned him,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.38,0:19:17.87,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,you pretended to be Eisaku \Nand went to the park,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.17,0:19:21.22,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,though it's amusing that you ended \Nup in two places at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.39,0:19:26.60,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,However, construction at \NDongaraji Temple began,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.10,0:19:29.35,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and your treasure was in \Ndanger of being dug up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.73,0:19:31.78,DCItalic,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Stop construction immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.78,0:19:33.86,DCItalic,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't, you'll be cursed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.50,0:19:36.48,DCMain,RYOZEN,0000,0000,0000,,You lumps of worldly desire!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.59,0:19:41.98,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san, you were right. \NThe two cases were connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.98,0:19:43.84,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,So then...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.84,0:19:46.08,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Where did he bury the backpack?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.58,0:19:47.87,DCMain,EISAKU,0000,0000,0000,,Where was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.08,0:19:50.37,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.74,0:19:56.11,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The robber fled here to escape the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.77,0:20:00.34,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He thought he would bury the \Nmoney he stole to hide it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.59,0:20:04.84,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, he chose a place \Nwhere no one would see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.66,0:20:09.77,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Where no one would see him?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.77,0:20:12.85,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,That would mean not even Eisaku saw him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.14,0:20:14.16,DCMain,GINTA,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.16,0:20:15.19,DCMain,GINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.82,0:20:22.20,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Shishido thought no one would see \Nhim there, but Eisaku-san did.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.42,0:20:27.86,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It could only have been there \Nbehind that ginkgo tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.37,0:20:32.71,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But Eisaku wouldn't have been \Nable to see him behind that tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.94,0:20:37.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,While wandering around that night, Eisaku \Ndidn't come directly to Dongaraji Temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.55,0:20:39.50,DCMain,RYOZEN,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.50,0:20:40.80,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Where was he, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.00,0:20:48.80,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Not even Shishido expected someone \Nto be on the roof at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.68,0:21:00.48,DCItalic,KINTA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Dad! Are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.28,0:21:05.25,DCItalic,GINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,I found him, Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.25,0:21:07.24,DCItalic,KINTA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make us worry so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.79,0:21:10.08,DCItalic,EISAKU,0000,0000,0000,,He was burying a backpack.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.30,0:21:11.35,DCItalic,KINTA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.02,0:21:13.08,DCItalic,GINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.33,0:21:15.64,DCMain,GINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.64,0:21:19.96,DCMain,GINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,he did mention that the view of the \Nsunset from up there was exceptional.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.20,0:21:23.97,DCMain,KINTA,0000,0000,0000,,He'd go up there all the time, \Nso he must've that evening, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.65,0:21:28.84,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,It's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.97,0:21:34.53,DCMain,EISAKU,0000,0000,0000,,That's it. It was here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.53,0:21:36.78,DCMain,KINTA,0000,0000,0000,,You've already seen it. It's too late now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.78,0:21:37.56,DCMain,GINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.83,0:21:40.13,DCMain,RYOZEN,0000,0000,0000,,You're still talking, you damned fools?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.39,0:23:10.82,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.10,0:23:16.12,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The head priest said he wouldn't mention the \Nphone threat if they agreed to work for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.45,0:23:27.34,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Pull yourselves together.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.23,0:23:34.05,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, Eisaku-san seems happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.71,0:23:37.20,DCMain,KINTA,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, pull yourself together.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.79,0:23:39.06,DCMain,GINSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,You, too, Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.02,0:24:09.05,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.22,0:23:47.52,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.71,0:23:52.03,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ai-chan...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.70,0:23:57.16,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,All right! I accept the job!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.07,0:23:59.95,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They're both here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.32,0:24:03.10,DCMain,AKIMICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Shall I have him come to \Nyour table when he returns?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.10,0:24:04.54,DCMain,HIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.91,0:24:06.07,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yoko-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.79,0:24:09.05,DCMain,HIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Asuka-san! Asuka-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.05,0:24:15.05,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The Suspects Are a Passionate Couple (Part 1)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.64,0:24:14.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is "The Suspects \NAre a Passionate Couple (Part 1)!"
